<title>USA: U.S.Transportation FY 1996 oper shr loss.</title>
<headline>U.S.Transportation FY 1996 oper shr loss.</headline>
<dateline>ELMSFORD, N.Y. 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>(In thousands except per share data)</p>
<p>					  (audited)</p>
<p>							 For the Twelve Months</p>
<p>							 Ended December 31,</p>
<p>							   1996	1995</p>
<p>Revenues:					 $21,509,751 $13,670,321</p>
<p>Income (loss) from Operations:	     (2,816,296)  1,389,936</p>
<p>Total other income (expense), net	 $  (456,939) $ (592,694)</p>
<p>Income (Loss) from continuing operations before</p>
<p>   income taxes				  (3,276,235)    797,242</p>
<p>Income tax expense (benefit)		    750,000   $(364,000)</p>
<p>Income (Loss) from continuing operations</p>
<p>   (carried forward)			  $(4,026,235) $1,161,242</p>
<p>(Loss) from discontinued operations	(2,668,216)    (37,324)</p>
<p>Net Income (Loss):			    $(6,694,451) $1,123,918</p>
<p>Less: Preferred Dividends			 169,335     191,700</p>
<p>Net Income (Loss) Applicable to Common</p>
<p>   Stockholders				 $(6,863,786)   $932,218</p>
<p>Earnings (Loss) Per Common Share:</p>
<p>   Income from continuing operations	    $(.97)	 $.53</p>
<p>   Discontinued operations			   (.62)	 (.02)</p>
<p>Earnings (Loss) Per Common Share		 $(1.59)	 $.51</p>
<p>Weighted Average Shares:			4,303,869   1,823,588</p>
<p>NOTES: FY 1996 income from continuing operations was $1,997,090 when corrected for non-recurring items that include the following:</p>
<p>     -    $215,500 loss on settlement of MountainView note receivable;</p>
<p>     -    $339,969 for a write-off of notes and other receivables;</p>
<p>     -    $750,000 write-off of deferred tax asset;</p>
<p>     -    $1,562,500 for issuance of 1,000,000 common shares related to</p>
<p>	    officer employment contract;</p>
<p>     -    $680,000 for conversion of preferred stock (valuation</p>
<p>	    differential);</p>
<p>     -    $782,410 write-down of ATAB's intangible assets as a result</p>
<p>	    of management's determination of impairment to future</p>
<p>	    profitability</p>
<p>     -    $657,250 of operating losses relating to a contract assumed</p>
<p>	    with the Krogel acquisition;</p>
<p>     -    $441,038 in interest expense for a bridge loan; and</p>
<p>     -    $594,659 in non-recurring consulting expenses.</p>
<p>NOTES: Also there was a loss from discontinued operations of $2,668,215 for operations of the entertainment subsidiaries and of Automated Solutions Inc, the airbag manufacturing subsidiary. These discontinued segments both sold in Q1 1997, the entertainment segment for 850,000 shares of Packaging Plus Inc and and Automated Solutions for notes and cash totaling about $5,950,000.</p>
<p>The subsequent reported gain on these sales will exceed $1.2 million.</p>
<p>Full co name is U.S. Transportation Systems Inc.</p>
